                <note rend="inline" type="source">741.91/23: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cheat Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-18T19:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 18, 1919, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received August 19, 2.22 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2831. At interview this afternoon for that purpose Curzon states that French
                    sentiment seems hostile to Anglo-Persian agreement and <pb facs="0785" n="700"
                        xml:id="pg_700"/> French Minister at Teheran disposed to foment
                    dissatisfaction, in which he hopes for assistance of American Minister. Requests
                    mat latter be put on guard and asked to preserve friendly attitude.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
